What consequences, great, small, short-term, near-term, geopolitical,
domestic, would this have?

Quoted from Kai Bird,
"Republican minority leader, Senator William White, boldly declared on
July3 , 1945, that the Pacific war might end "quickly" if only Truman
would clarify surrender terms (to indicate the Japanese monarchy would
be preserved). This view was echoed by former President Herbert
Hoover, who wrote Truman in May and early June that he, too, favored a
clarification. This very newspaper (the Washington Post) published a
series of editorials in the spring of 1945 urging such a course on
Truman. Obviously, if Truman decided to do so, he could have issued a
clarification with the political support of his Republican opposition."
